const faqs = [
  { q: 'Does the Logitech Brio 4K work with Mac?', a: 'Yes. The Brio is UVC-compliant and works plug-and-play on macOS, Windows, ChromeOS, and most Linux distributions. The webcam itself works without drivers, but Logi Tune software (which unlocks 4K, zoom presets, and color tuning) is available for both Mac and Windows.' },
  { q: 'Is the Logitech Brio 4K worth it over the C920?', a: 'For most remote workers yes. The Brio shoots 4K30 and 1080p60 versus the C920s 1080p30, has RightLight 3 HDR for backlit rooms, includes a 5x digital zoom, and adds Windows Hello IR. The image quality difference is visible on every call. If you only take a few calls per week in a well-lit room, the C920 at $69 is fine.' },
  { q: 'Does the Brio 4K need USB 3.0?', a: 'Yes for 4K30 video. On a USB 2.0 port the Brio drops to 1080p30. Most modern laptops and monitors have USB 3.0 or USB-C, so this is rarely an issue. The Brio ships with both a USB-A to USB-C cable and a USB-C to USB-C cable in the box.' },
